data.title: Last Name Mcmanus: origin, history, and heritage
data.meta_description: Discover the origin and history of the last name Mcmanus. Learn more about the origin of your last name, its history, and your family heritage.
data.text:
The last name "McManus" originates from Ireland. It is an anglicized form of the Gaelic surname "Mac Mánuis," which means "son of Manus." Manus is a variant of Magnús, derived from the Latin name "Magnus," meaning "great" or "large." In Irish history, the MacManus clan was associated with the province of Ulster. Over time, many people with the surname McManus migrated from Ireland to various parts of the world, particularly the United Kingdom, the United States, Canada, and Australia.
